1227A 101st Legislative Session 1227
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1227
AMENDME NT 1227A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Weems
1 An Act to increase the annual fee required of an owner of an electric motor vehicle.
2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
3 Section 1. That § 32-5-188 be AMENDED:
4 32-5-188. In addition to the license fees paid pursuant to the provisions of this
5 chapter for a motor vehicle, the owner of an electric motor vehicle shall pay an annual fee
6 of fifty one hundred dollars. The fee shall must be paid at the time of annual registration
7 as otherwise provided in this chapter. However, the The license fee imposed by this section
8 does not apply to any motorcycle propelled by an electric motor, if the license fee is paid
9 pursuant to § 32-5-9.
10 For the purposes of this section, the term, "electric motor vehicle," means a
11 noncommercial motor vehicle that is propelled by for which the only source of propulsion
12 is an electric motor that draws electricity from a battery that is capable of being recharged
13 from an external source of electricity, and that which may be legally operated on the
14 interstate highways in this state and eligible for registration pursuant to the laws of this
15 state. The electric motor vehicle shall must have been made by a manufacturer primarily
16 for use on public streets, roads, and highways and meets must meet National Highway
17 Traffic Safety Administration standards included provided in 49 C.F.R. § 571 as of (January
18 1, 2021).
19 The fees received pursuant to this section shall must be deposited in the state
20 highway fund.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

